			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/blog.music.aol.com/media/2012/05/donna-summer-639-051712.jpg" alt="" width="500" /></p>
<h2><em>No One Will Ever Forget This Voice</em></h2>
<p><object width="480" height="274"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/7oO0Kj4yeRg?version=3&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/7oO0Kj4yeRg?version=3&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="480" height="274" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object></p>
<p><strong>This was the original theme song for BadGalsRadio.com</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Just Listen to her voice &#8211; she had magnificent range and strength. It was taken from us, as she was just reaching her peak.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: justify;"><em>Donna will always be remembered as another casualty of 911.</em></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Her apartment was near the world trade center when it collapsed in september of 2001. She said to many people that the lung cancer she sucumbed to was due to the close proximity of her apartment to the world trade center. It&#8217;s reported that she complained about the smell and the heaviness of the air.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Eventually she moved out of the apartment &#8211; but not before the damage had been done.  She relocated and lived the rest of her life in florida.  when she was diagnosed with Lung Cancer, she told many people that she believed it originated from the 911 dust;  that drove her from her beloved new york.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We saw her perform in ny at the Roseland Ballroom in the late 1970&#8242;s.  We also caught her sneaking in on a Sylvester set at Paradise Garage in ny.  It was always a party when she showed up on the set. Her fun sweet manner made her an instant icon. She was loved by all who met and knew her.  We can never forget her and we&#8217;ll forever associate her voice with Good Times.</p>
<h2><em>Donna Summer Saldano will forever be our voice of Summer,</em></h2>
<p><img src="http://badgals-radio.com/re-sig.jpg" alt="" /></p>
