			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Click this graphic to see the fullsize readable copy on it's home site." href="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m410dcRQ6s1ql6jblo1_1280.png" target="_blank"><img src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m410dcRQ6s1ql6jblo1_1280.png" alt="" width="500" /></a></p>
<p><strong>Please Click this graphic to see it fullsized on it&#8217;s home site ProPublica</strong></p>
<p>This chart is a comparison between President Barack Obama and Past President G W. Bush regarding their stands on on torture, surveillance, and detention in an infographic <a href="https://www.propublica.org/special/obama-vs-bush-on-national-security-timeline" target="_blank">from ProPublica</a>.</p>
<p>This chart puts it in language anyone can understand. Bush Was a Bloody Bully; and Obama is trying to Get Along.</p>
<p><strong>Take a Look at This Chart &#8211; From NPR Today</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/money/2012/05/14/152671813/50-years-of-government-spending-in-1-graph?sc=fb&amp;cc=fp"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m42ipi0ypj1qd9dz2o1_500.jpg" alt="" width="462" height="700" /></a></p>
<div>
<blockquote><p><strong>50 Years of Government Spending, in 1 Graph</strong></p>
<p>(via <a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/money/2012/05/14/152671813/50-years-of-government-spending-in-1-graph?sc=fb&amp;cc=fp" target="_blank">50 Years of Government Spending, In 1 Graph : Planet Money : NPR</a>)</p></blockquote>
</div>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>You can clearly see that America has spent more playing badly than providing for it&#8217;s own internal needs. Why ?</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This is what should be asked of the folks who were in charge during these peak spending years for defense.  Until america puts Education, and Social Welfare programs into it&#8217;s priority list &#8211; life in america will continue to slip into the red zone.  The chart shows clearly how much this small amount of money matters to the budgeters &#8211; at the end of the day.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>How can those who are elected think that social welfare and education are to follow defense spending ?</strong></p>
<h2 style="text-align: justify;">What Happened to <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Sound</em></span> Domestic Policy ?</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If social welfare programs and education are ignored, how will the defense picture be impacted;  should be the question at this point.  How can you train soldiers if they don&#8217;t have primary education &#8211; which in america is a right. But not according to the actions of congress; If they continue to cut funding &#8211; as they clearly do each session.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Today this was in <a href="http://theatlantic.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">the Atlantic</a></strong> -</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;">“The other part of the student debt crisis is all of the debt that students aren’t taking on because they’re not going to college. College grads still earn more, work longer, and are employed at higher rates than everybody else. Their investment — that is, their debt — benefits the country at large in the form of a more-skilled workforce, higher productivity, higher GDP, more taxes, and so on. Newspapers can’t report on this part of the student debt crisis, because there is no headline statistic to report on. You can’t put a number on how much money some promising inner-city student is giving up in lifetime earnings by not attending college or how much it’s taking away from federal income taxes through 2030. But just because those statistics are invisible don’t mean they’re not real.”</p>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td valign="top">—</td>
<td valign="top"><strong><a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2012/05/the-student-debt-crisis-we-dont-talk-about/257146/">Derek Thompson, on America’s trillion-dollar student debt crisis.</a></strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>They can&#8217;t even agree on helping those who are the poorest &#8211; student loan debtors</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Did you know <span style="color: #ff0000;">they can now garnish your social security and disability payments</span> from the government &#8211; <span style="color: #ff0000;">for back student loans.</span>   </strong></em><strong>and <span style="text-decoration: underline;">yes they are doing it</span> now.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;">How do you feed the poor who are destined to join the miltary as their step up in life, if you cut primary food programs such as food stamps and school lunch subsidys ?  where will the soldiers come from who can&#8217;t read to operate the machinery ?  and who will teach them to read when they have to operate the machinery ?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>This was in <a href="http://think-progress.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Think Progress</a> today - </strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><a href="http://thinkprogress.org/education/2012/05/13/483363/5-mindblowing-facts-about-student-debt/" rel="nofollow">FACT: The number of students who have to go into debt to get a bachelor’s degree has risen from 45% in 1993 to 94% today.</a></strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>These are the critical questions that need to be asked of those who place military spending at the top of the budget food chain</strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>This was in<a href="http://azspot.net/" target="_blank"> the AZSpot </a>Today</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a id="high_res_link_22777738928" href="http://24.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m3rbcub9ZR1qz4sr8o1_1280.png"><img src="http://badgals-radio.com/wp-content/uploads/HLIC/7525223a7d2d5aa90a3ff8592cf8dd11.png" alt="" width="500" height="539" /></a></p>
<div>
<p><a href="http://jessecurtis.blogspot.com/2012/05/reality-check.html">reality check</a></p>
</div>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We believe that if generals continue to run the united states budget; pretty soon there will be no more soldiers or citizens. They&#8217;ll all die from hunger and the lack of skills employable skills.  Just ask a now citizen former soldier &#8211; who&#8217;s homeless.</p>
<h2>America, Have You <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Any</em></span> Manners Left ?</h2>
<p><img src="http://badgals-radio.com/re-sig.jpg" alt="" /></p>
]]></content:encoded>
