		<description><![CDATA[Today we should all remember Sybrina Fulton &#8211; the mother who lost her child Trayvon. Please Watch the Video for Sybrina&#8217;s Message We Join Sybrina in asking for a second look at Stand Your Ground Laws across the US. Call your legislators if you live in a stand your ground state and ask them to [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment_tv_tvblog/files/2012/03/PX00100_91.jpg" alt="" width="500" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Today we should all remember Sybrina Fulton &#8211; the mother who lost her child Trayvon.</strong></p>
<h2>Please Watch the Video for Sybrina&#8217;s Message</h2>
<p><object width="500" height="284" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/m_4HHcOHBfU?version=3&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed width="500" height="284" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/m_4HHcOHBfU?version=3&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0" allowFullScreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" /></object></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We Join Sybrina in asking for a second look at Stand Your Ground Laws across the US. Call your legislators if you live in a stand your ground state and ask them to re-examine the laws and to put in place safeguards so that sentencing and definition match the actual crime.  More on that shortly</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://i158.photobucket.com/albums/t106/OnlyObvious/ALEC/Stand_your_ground_States_500.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We also want to ask you to remember another victim of the Stand Your Ground laws in Florida &#8211; Sister Marissa Alexander. Her husband had previously been placed under an order of protection.  Yet he came to the home of Marissa to abuse her once again.  He told her He Was Going To Kill Her.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://www.forgottenmajority.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Marissa-and-child1.jpeg" alt="" width="450" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">With a four day old baby, Marissa didn&#8217;t want to take another beating, so she stood her ground. Now she&#8217;s facing twenty years in jail for doing so.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong><em>Bear In Mind that She Didn&#8217;t Shoot Him &#8211; and that He Told Her He Was Going To Kill Her</em></strong></p></blockquote>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This should tell you just how unevenly this law is applied. If it applied for George Zimmerman to kill Trayvon Martin; and not for Marissa Alexander to fire <em>a warning shot</em> at her already convicted abuser; we need to understand why.</p>
<p><img src="http://bossip.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/photo1-e1336834193171.png" alt="" width="500" /></p>
<h2 style="text-align: justify;">There Is Something Very Wrong With This Picture</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">There can be no more ignoring and pretending. It&#8217;s time to become a voice in the discussion on these deadly laws. Otherwise we will just continue to be victims <em>for Standing Our Ground</em>.</p>
<p><object id="flashObj" width="486" height="412" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="flashVars" value="videoId=1619486156001&amp;playerID=35104629001&amp;playerKey=AQ~~,AAAACCo2HcE~,Xq6bv4z8O3Vypjqp8SRaPWSEmhvW8Iso&amp;domain=embed&amp;dynamicStreaming=true" /><param name="base" value="http://admin.brightcove.com" /><param name="seamlesstabbing" value="false" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="swLiveConnect" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9?isVid=1" /><param name="flashvars" value="videoId=1619486156001&amp;playerID=35104629001&amp;playerKey=AQ~~,AAAACCo2HcE~,Xq6bv4z8O3Vypjqp8SRaPWSEmhvW8Iso&amp;domain=embed&amp;dynamicStreaming=true" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="swliveconnect" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="pluginspage" value="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash" /><embed id="flashObj" width="486" height="412" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9?isVid=1" flashVars="videoId=1619486156001&amp;playerID=35104629001&amp;playerKey=AQ~~,AAAACCo2HcE~,Xq6bv4z8O3Vypjqp8SRaPWSEmhvW8Iso&amp;domain=embed&amp;dynamicStreaming=true" base="http://admin.brightcove.com" seamlesstabbing="false" allowFullScreen="true" swLiveConnect="true" allowScriptAccess="always" flashvars="videoId=1619486156001&amp;playerID=35104629001&amp;playerKey=AQ~~,AAAACCo2HcE~,Xq6bv4z8O3Vypjqp8SRaPWSEmhvW8Iso&amp;domain=embed&amp;dynamicStreaming=true" allowfullscreen="true" swliveconnect="true" allowscriptaccess="always" pluginspage="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash" /></object></p>
<blockquote><p><a href="http://downtownjax.firstcoastnews.com/news/news/77605-marissa-alexanders-retrial-motion-denied">Marissa Alexander learned her numerous motions for a retrial were denied Thursday morning by Circuit Court Judge James Daniel.</a></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A packed Duval County courtroom listened as the judge heard arguments as to why Alexander should be granted a new trial.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Earlier Thursday morning, a group of supporters gathered to hold signs and hope to encourage the judge to grant Alexander a new trial.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Former victims of domestic violence were among the group, which was there to speak out not only on behalf of Alexander, but for other victims of domestic violence as well. Their fear is that by prosecuting Alexander, other victims may become fearful of leaving an abusive relationship or defending themselves.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Marissa Alexander was convicted on three counts of aggravated assault after firing a warning shot at her ex-husband inside their home in August 2010.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>At the time, Alexander had already taken out a protective order against her ex-husband earlier that year when he was arrested for physically abusing her.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">So when a fight started in their master bedroom, Alexander told police she feared for her life. Motions filed by the State Attorney&#8217;s office state Alexander was the aggressor, not her husband. However, her defense attorney argues Alexander&#8217;s ex-husband said he was going to kill her.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Alexander&#8217;s attorney, Kevin Cobbin, wanted a new trial based on Florida&#8217;s Stand Your Ground law and said that it should have applied in this case.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Judge Daniel disagreed in making his ruling before a packed courtroom.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">After the hearing, Cobbin said the Stand Your Ground law is not always applied fairly.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>&#8220;The law was made for people like Ms. Alexander. They did not make it for people running around on the streets shooting people. They made it for women in their homes trying to defended themselves against abusive mean men,&#8221; said Cobbin.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Instead of leaving, Alexander did return to the kitchen and fired a single shot into the ceiling with her ex-husband and his two small children in the room.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">State Attorney Angela Corey says she met with Alexander and her attorney before the trial, along with the victims, to personally review the circumstances of the shooting and the self defense claim.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Corey says the defendant, Alexander, was offered a plea deal of three years. Corey said Alexander did not accept the deal.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Prosecutor Nick Lake said following the hearing, &#8220;The jury decided she was not in fear when she fired the gun. She went back to his house, alone, and committed a domestic battery on him (ex-husband).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Marissa Alexander&#8217;s sentencing has been scheduled for Friday, May 11. Her attorney, Kevin Cobbin, says he plans to file an appeal following her sentencing.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Alexander faces a sentence of 20 years in prison.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2>When will we stop being the planned victims ?</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In the wake of the killing of  Trayvon Martin &#8230; The Koch bros. who manufacture paper products are paying for Trayvons killer George Zimmerman&#8217;s legal fees. They say it&#8217;s because they feel he had legal right to bear arms and shoot Trayvon.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">We are asking that people everywhere ban together with us and pass this information on and not purchase any of the following items because your money will be paying for Zimmermans legal fees.</p>
<h2>Please do not purchase any of the following items :</h2>
<ul>
<li>Angel soft toilet paper</li>
<li>Brawny paper towel</li>
<li>Dixie plates,bowls napkins cups</li>
<li>Mardi gras napkins and towels</li>
<li>Quilted northern toilet paper</li>
<li>Soft and gentle toilet paper</li>
<li>Sparkle napkins</li>
<li>Vanity fair napkins</li>
<li>Zero napkins</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>We must all remember our sisters today.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Please re post and re send this message to everyone so that we can work this out quickly.</strong></p>
<h2><em>A Happy and Blessed Mother&#8217;s Day to you all</em></h2>
<p><img src="http://badgals-radio.com/re-sig.jpg" alt="" /></p>
]]></content:encoded>
